./docs/sprint-memos/7h-42-V7d-split-review.codex.log:3952:./docs/sprint-memos/7h-41-V6d-roadmap.codex.log:5158:   435	- 2026-04-27 [orchestration][parallel-write-3way-conflict-pattern] **Three write workers extending the same public function signature + same enum produce 8-12 conflict regions per merge — plan for it.** Sprint 7h-39 V1+V2+V3 all extended `compute_vault_diff` kwargs and all re-added duplicate `ChangeKind.SKIP` directives. Mitigations: (a) tell each worker that signature kwarg additions are PARENT's merge job, not theirs (helps); (b) consolidate enum additions into a separate parent-only commit BEFORE fan-out (best); (c) when conflicts arrive, rewrite the file as a full-file `Write` with helpers in canonical order rather than line-by-line conflict-marker editing (faster and produces a clean diff for review). 3-way merge wall ~5min with these.
./docs/sprint-memos/7h-42-V7d-split-review.codex.log:3953:./docs/sprint-memos/7h-40-V5d-operator-bootstrap.codex.log:6245:   435	- 2026-04-27 [orchestration][parallel-write-3way-conflict-pattern] **Three write workers extending the same public function signature + same enum produce 8-12 conflict regions per merge — plan for it.** Sprint 7h-39 V1+V2+V3 all extended `compute_vault_diff` kwargs and all re-added duplicate `ChangeKind.SKIP` directives. Mitigations: (a) tell each worker that signature kwarg additions are PARENT's merge job, not theirs (helps); (b) consolidate enum additions into a separate parent-only commit BEFORE fan-out (best); (c) when conflicts arrive, rewrite the file as a full-file `Write` with helpers in canonical order rather than line-by-line conflict-marker editing (faster and produces a clean diff for review). 3-way merge wall ~5min with these.
./docs/sprint-memos/7h-42-V7d-split-review.codex.log:3965:  5152	   429	- 2026-04-27 [orchestration][live-worker-may-bypass-linked-worktree-ref] **A codex live-mode worker can land its commit on `origin/<branch>` without updating the linked-worktree's local branch ref or clearing its working-tree diff.** Symptoms after worker reports DONE: `git ls-remote origin <branch>` shows new SHA, but in the linked worktree `git log` shows the OLD base SHA and `git status` shows the same files as " M" (modified vs HEAD). Cause: live-mode codex appears to commit via plumbing or its own gitdir handling (different from offline-bg's auto-add-dir patch from LESSON `[orchestration][parent-commit]`). Recovery: skip the worktree entirely — parent merges `origin/<branch>` directly from the primary repo with `git merge --no-ff origin/<branch>`, then runs pytest in primary, pushes, and `git worktree remove --force` the dirty linked tree. The dirty diff there is just a stale copy of what's now on main, so `--force` removal is safe. Don't try to reconcile the linked worktree's HEAD — it's a distraction. Future fix in `codex_live.sh`: print local HEAD + remote HEAD after commit so the parent can spot the divergence in the launcher log immediately.
./docs/sprint-memos/7h-42-V7d-split-review.codex.log:3969:  5156	   433	- 2026-04-27 [orchestration][archive-codex-artifacts] **Every sprint's codex prompts (`/tmp/dsk-*.md`) and worker logs (`/tmp/codex-*.log`) are ephemeral; archive eagerly to `docs/sprint-memos/`.** A single reboot otherwise loses cite-rich prompt patterns that took ~120 LOC each to write. Parent step ~3min/sprint: copy `*.prompt.md` files plus `tail -200..400` of write-worker logs (full logs of readonly memo workers stay reasonable). Established 7h-39 with retroactive backfill of 7h-37 + 7h-38. Future agents reuse the prompt patterns as templates and read the post-mortem tails to learn how previous workers self-fixed bugs during live runs.
./docs/sprint-memos/7h-42-V7d-split-review.codex.log:3971:  5158	   435	- 2026-04-27 [orchestration][parallel-write-3way-conflict-pattern] **Three write workers extending the same public function signature + same enum produce 8-12 conflict regions per merge — plan for it.** Sprint 7h-39 V1+V2+V3 all extended `compute_vault_diff` kwargs and all re-added duplicate `ChangeKind.SKIP` directives. Mitigations: (a) tell each worker that signature kwarg additions are PARENT's merge job, not theirs (helps); (b) consolidate enum additions into a separate parent-only commit BEFORE fan-out (best); (c) when conflicts arrive, rewrite the file as a full-file `Write` with helpers in canonical order rather than line-by-line conflict-marker editing (faster and produces a clean diff for review). 3-way merge wall ~5min with these.
