docs/sprint-memos/7h-37-S3-lock-design.codex.log:2079:  1713	- 2026-04-27 `[orchestration][parallel-codex-fanout]` 4 codex offline-bg + 1 Task subagent in parallel produced 4 cross-cited memos in ~5min wall-clock and surfaced 1 immediately-landable schema drift fix (`bffa01b`); wall-clock cost dominated by single-worker latency, so N parallel ≈ 1× sequential time. Pattern: when investigation prompts are independent, well-scoped, and cite-required, parallel readonly fan-out is high-ROI relative to serial codex_offline + serial parent reads.
